            "words":[
                {"w":"3. "},
                {"w":"There is no word in Arabic corresponding to \"a\" in English as in \"this is a book\". The n-sound at the end of the Arabic noun(kitabu-n, baitu-n, masjidu-n) is the Arabic indefinite article corresponding to the English \"a\"/\"an\". This n-sound is called tanwin  "}               
